&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Social Media Strategist&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Sociallyin | Atlanta, GA (Remote) | $80,000 - $100,000&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re hiring a Senior Social Media Strategist to help shape the future of strategy at Sociallyin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a role for someone who simply manages content calendars or writes social media recommendations.&amp;nbsp;We&#39;re looking for someone who understands people, culture, consumer behavior, marketing, and business. Someone who can sit across from a Fortune 500 marketing leader, earn their trust, and help them make smarter decisions.&amp;nbsp;Someone who can identify opportunities before clients ask for them.&amp;nbsp;Someone who sees around corners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Sociallyin&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SociallyIn is a 100% social media-focused agency. Not &quot;social plus a bunch of other stuff.&quot; Just social.&amp;nbsp;For more than 15 years, we&#39;ve helped brands navigate the ever-changing social landscape through strategy, content production, community management, paid social advertising, influencer marketing, and social selling.&amp;nbsp;We&#39;re 50+ people strong, fully remote, and work with brands ranging from challenger startups to enterprise organizations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As social media continues evolving faster than ever and AI reshapes how marketers work, we&#39;re investing heavily in the future of strategy.&amp;nbsp;That&#39;s where you come in. We&#39;re hiring a Senior Social Media Strategist to own client relationships, drive strategy, and grow accounts. We want someone who&#39;s genuinely curious about where this industry is headed and inherently, naturally, gloriously social, both online and off!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Social Media Strategist serves as one of the agency&#39;s strategic leaders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll help guide social media strategy across multiple client accounts, influence marketing decisions, contribute to agency thought leadership, support new business efforts, and elevate strategic thinking across the organization.&amp;nbsp;You&#39;ll work closely with Account Management, Creative, Community Management, Paid Media, Influencer Marketing, and Leadership to ensure our clients aren&#39;t just keeping up with social media, they&#39;re staying ahead of it. You&#39;ll report directly to agency leadership and have meaningful influence over how strategy evolves inside Sociallyin.&amp;nbsp;This role is ideal for someone who loves solving problems, understanding people, analyzing trends, and helping brands win.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and lead social media strategies across multiple client accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business objectives into actionable social marketing plans that drive measurable outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities for audience growth, content innovation, community development, and platform expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create strategic frameworks that improve consistency and elevate thinking across the agency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted advisor to client stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead strategic conversations, planning sessions, workshops, and quarterly business reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Challenge assumptions when necessary and provide recommendations backed by data, experience, and sound judgment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships that position Sociallyin as a strategic partner, not just a vendor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Turn performance data into actionable recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
