&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://sociallyin.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/socialmediahiringgraphic.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1983&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Social Media Account Manager&lt;/strong&gt; SociallyIn | Atlanta, GA (Remote) | $75,000–$90,000&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re hiring a Social Media Account Manager, and this isn&#39;t a typical AM role.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SociallyIn is a 100% social media-focused agency. Not &quot;social plus a bunch of other stuff.&quot; Just social. We&#39;ve been operating for 15 years, we&#39;re 50 people strong, and we&#39;re actively investing in how AI changes the way agencies work. We&#39;re hiring a Social Media Account Manager to own client relationships, drive strategy, and grow accounts. We want someone who&#39;s genuinely curious about where this industry is headed and inherently, naturally, gloriously social, both online and off!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a senior-track role for someone who wants real ownership, not a glorified project manager seat. You are responsible for managing and strengthening relationships with our clients from start to finish.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the charge for client accounts with strategy, content curation, distribution, and engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4-8 client accounts as the primary point of contact and strategic lead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading day-to-day communication for multiple client accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building strong, trusted relationships with clients and internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Social strategy development, content direction, and performance optimization across all major platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influencer identification, outreach, and campaign management when applicable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading client calls, presentations, reporting discussions, and strategic conversations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing projects, timelines, deliverables, and cross-functional coordination&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Client growth, identifying expansion opportunities, and making the case for them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-functional collaboration with creative production, paid media, and strategy&amp;nbsp; teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Social listening for trending content, conversations, topics, events, and news&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring clients feel supported, informed, and confident in the partnership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay updated with industry trends, algorithm changes, and platform updates to ensure best results for clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor, analyze, and report social media data to track performance against key performance indicators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance reporting and storytelling that translates data into decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What success looks like in 90 days:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve built trust with every client in your book&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve identified at least one optimization or growth opportunity per account&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re actively experimenting with AI tools to sharpen your work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your clients see you as a strategic partner, not a vendor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where this role can go.&lt;/strong&gt; Our strongest AMs grow into Senior AM, Group Account Director, or Strategy Lead roles within 2-3 years. We promote from within first. If you want to eventually run a team, own a client vertical, or shape agency strategy - there&#39;s a clear path here, and we&#39;ll build it with you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring to the table:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-8 years of social media account management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-3 years of agency experience required&lt;/li&gt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sociallyin is a leading social media marketing agency dedicated to delivering exceptional services to our clients. We are currently seeking an experienced and knowledgeable Social Media Designer to join our team in developing engaging social media content for our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role and Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Greet each day as an opportunity to blend creativity, unique client knowledge and solid design skills to produce industry-leading content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create high-quality social media-focused graphic designs, 2D motion graphics, and video edits, utilizing Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator, Photoshop, Premiere Pro, After Effects), Figma, CapCut and Google Suite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and design custom visual assets, including icons and general vector elements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform video editing tasks to produce polished and engaging final products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to project ideation and brainstorming sessions, offering creative input and design solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively participate in client presentations, confidently presenting design work and concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently manage workload, proactively communicating project updates, bandwidth availability, and resource needs to relevant teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5 years of experience with creating visuals for social media platforms
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Illustration (general, i.e. icons, basic swoops, arrows, etc.), graphic design, 2D motion design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in design software such as:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator, Photoshop, Premiere Pro, After Effects), CapCut, Figma&amp;nbsp;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Overlord or willingness to learn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong video editing skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have a computer capable of running multiple Adobe software programs simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;***A PORTFOLIO MUST BE INCLUDED TO BE CONSIDERED FOR THIS POSITION.***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;$50,000-$60,000, DOE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$350/yr Learning Credit (Books, Events, Classes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spotify Subscription ($10/m Value)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gym Membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;11 Company Recognized Holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uncapped PTO/Sick/Birthday/Etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical Insurance ($300/mo covered by Sociallyin)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dental/Vision Insurance (offered)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible Equipment Plans&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(k) + 2% Match&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And more!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For any questions or additional information, please contact&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:hr@sociallyin.com&quot;&gt;hr@sociallyin.com&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
